---
const findings = [
  {
    accent: 'teal',
    title: 'Reporting Without Insight',
    body: "Executives get reports every month yet still can't answer simple questions. Where are costs rising? Which customers drive them? Which activities create value?",
    punch: 'The data exists. The insight doesn\'t.',
  },
  {
    accent: 'coral',
    title: 'Software Driving the Business',
    body: 'Processes have gradually evolved around the limitations of existing software rather than around how the business would ideally operate.',
    punch: 'The software becomes the operating model.',
  },
  {
    accent: 'teal',
    title: 'Business Problems in Disguise',
    body: 'Organizations start by shopping for software. The real issue is usually reporting, operations or workflow.',
    punch: 'Technology is proposed before the problem is understood.',
  },
  {
    accent: 'coral',
    title: 'Automation in the Wrong Place',
    body: 'Teams automate individual tasks before understanding the workflow those tasks belong to.',
    punch: 'Simplifying a process often beats automating it.',
  },
  {
    accent: 'teal',
    title: 'Building the Wrong Things',
    body: "Some capabilities create advantage. Others are long since solved. The challenge isn't whether to build.",
    punch: "It's deciding what deserves to be built.",
  },
  {
    accent: 'coral',
    title: 'AI Before Strategy',
    body: 'Most begin with "How can we use AI?" The better question is "Where would better decisions create the most value?"',
    punch: 'AI gets far more valuable once the problem is understood.',
  },
];
---

<section class="section section--dark findings" id="findings">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow on-dark">Recurring Findings</p>
      <h2>Patterns We See Again and Again</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Most organizations don't need more technology. They need greater clarity about how their business
        operates.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="findings__grid">
      {findings.map((f) => (
        <article class="finding reveal">
          <h3><span class="finding__dot" style={`background:var(--${f.accent})`}></span>{f.title}</h3>
          <p class="finding__body">{f.body}</p>
          <p class={`finding__punch finding__punch--${f.accent}`}>{f.punch}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="findings__banner reveal">
      Most organizations don't suffer from a lack of technology. They suffer from technology decisions made
      before the business problem was understood.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .findings__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
  }
  .finding {
    background: var(--ink-3);
    border: 1px solid var(--line-dark);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
  }
  .finding h3 { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.65rem; font-size: 1.3rem; margin-bottom: 0.9rem; }
  .finding__dot { width: 11px; height: 11px; border-radius: 50%; flex: none; }
  .finding__body { color: var(--text-on-dark-muted); margin-bottom: 1.1rem; }
  .finding__punch { font-weight: 700; font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3; }
  .finding__punch--teal { color: var(--teal-bright); }
  .finding__punch--coral { color: var(--coral-soft); }

  .findings__banner {
    background: var(--ink-2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 3vw, 1.75rem);
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    max-width: 44ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .findings__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
